Two Changes Needed
1. Update jaas.conf — Use Ticket Cache Instead of Keytab for MongoDB Section
com.sun.security.jgss.krb5.initiate {
    com.sun.security.auth.module.Krb5LoginModule required
    useTicketCache=true
    ticketCache="/tmp/krb5cc_kafkaconnect"
    renewTGT=false
    doNotPrompt=true
    useKeyTab=false
    debug=true;
};
Key changes:
useKeyTab=false — don't try to use keytab in Java
useTicketCache=true — use the ticket kinit already obtained
ticketCache="/tmp/krb5cc_kafkaconnect" — exact location kinit stored the ticket
2. Update entrypoint.sh KAFKA_OPTS — Keep Native GSS Flags
export KAFKA_OPTS="-Djava.security.krb5.conf=/opt/secrets/krb5/krb5.ini \
-Djava.security.auth.login.config=/opt/kafka-connect/config/jaas.conf \
-Djavax.security.auth.useSubjectCredsOnly=false \
-Dsun.security.jgss.native=true \
-Dsun.security.jgss.lib=/usr/lib64/libgssapi_krb5.so.2 \
-Djavax.net.ssl.trustStore=/opt/secrets/truststore/truststore.jks \
-Djavax.net.ssl.trustStorePassword=changeit \
-Dsun.security.krb5.debug=true"
3. Remove JCE Fix from Dockerfile
Since Java won't do crypto itself anymore, remove the problematic RUN JAVA_SEC block entirely:
FROM barclays-registry-prod-v4-uk.barcapint.com/barclays/ubi8:latest

LABEL prisma_email_alert="modemanuradhasai.shakti@barclays.com"

USER root
WORKDIR /opt

# Install Java 21 + Kerberos client tools
RUN dnf -y install java-21-openjdk-headless krb5-workstation && \
    dnf -y clean all && \
    rm -rf /var/cache/dnf

# Verify kerberos tools exist
RUN which kinit && which klist

# Copy Kafka + plugins
COPY kafka /opt/kafka
COPY plugins /opt/kafka/plugins

# Copy configs
COPY config/jaas.conf /opt/kafka-connect/config/jaas.conf
COPY config/worker.properties /opt/kafka-connect/config/worker.properties
COPY config/mongodb-sink.properties /opt/kafka-connect/config/mongodb-sink.properties

# Entrypoint
COPY entrypoint.sh /opt/kafka-connect/entrypoint.sh

# OpenShift permissions
RUN chmod +x /opt/kafka-connect/entrypoint.sh && \
    chmod -R g+rwX /opt/kafka /opt/kafka-connect && \
    chgrp -R 0 /opt/kafka /opt/kafka-connect

USER 1001
EXPOSE 8083
ENTRYPOINT ["/opt/kafka-connect/entrypoint.sh"]
Why This Will Work
Before:
jaas.conf → useKeyTab=true → Java tries AES256 crypto → FAILS ❌

After:
kinit → gets ticket using native lib → stores in /tmp/krb5cc_kafkaconnect
jaas.conf → useTicketCache=true → Java picks up existing ticket → NO crypto needed ✅
Make these changes, rebuild and redeploy!
